DEPENDENCY INJECTION/ AUTO WIRING
BEANS -
COMPONENT SCANNING - A process that runs when the boot application is started, looks for beans and provide them where they are needed.
- place all beans in the spring application context.
- Pool of beans and can be provided whenever they are needed.
- If the application lacks the beans it needs it fails to start up.



@SPRINGBOOTAPPLICATION
    @CONFIGURATION - Identifies a configuration class, where spring should look for beans during it configuration phase.
    @ComponentScan - Says from the point of project hierarchy and down look for beans and provide them where they are needed.
    @EnableAutoConfiguration - A process that spring boot uses when it starts up, provide all dependencies and defaults.